overview: The user aimed to enhance their sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for storing responses and developing an admin dashboard
  for data access. The agent thoroughly evaluated the existing codebase,
  identified the missing functionalities, and formulated a comprehensive plan.
  Key decisions involved utilizing NeonDB (PostgreSQL) as the database, defining
  a  model within Prisma, and establishing API endpoints
  for both saving and retrieving data. Initially, a custom session management
  system with HMAC-signed tokens was implemented for the admin dashboard's
  authentication. However, this approach was later refined to a simpler, more
  integrated solution using Next.js middleware for route protection and session
  handling. The implementation encompassed updating demographic fields, creating
  the database schema, developing API routes for responses and CSV export,
  building the login and dashboard pages, and integrating the database saving
  mechanism into the questionnaire submission flow. The agent also guided the
  user through the database setup process, ensuring correct environment variable
  configuration and successful Prisma migrations.
